  "NaCl solubility changes very little with temperature (nearly flat curve)": "",
  "NaCl is insoluble at temperatures below 100 degrees Celsius": "",
  "NaCl is a gas that becomes less soluble at higher temperatures": "",
  "NaCl only goes from 36 to 39 g/100 mL over an 80-degree temperature range, indicating its solubility curve is nearly flat. Temperature has little effect on NaCl solubility.": "",
  "A student heats 100 mL of water to 80 degrees C and dissolves 160 g of KNO3 (solubility at 80 degrees C is 170 g). She cools the solution to 20 degrees C (solubility is 30 g). How much KNO3 crystallizes out?": "",
